FBIS3-36652 "drsov026_a_94031" FBIS-SOV-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Japanese Vessels Admit Fishing, Border Violations LD0802103594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0936 GMT 8 Feb 94 LD0802103594 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] [Text] Moscow February 8 TASS -- Captains of two Japanese vessels detained on Monday by Russian border guard ships signed a protocol on the violation of the state border and illegal fishing in Russian territorial waters, ITAR-TASS learned on Tuesday from the press service of Russian border guard troops. At present, the vessels -- violators of the border, are lying at anchor at the Tyaginskaya Bay. The situation in the central part of the Sea of Okhotsk and in the direction of the South Kuril Islands is under tight control by Russian aviation and naval border guard troops, the press service said.
